channel.title: This SHOULD work but doesn't?
channel.description:
Okay so, I'm trying to add sailing to my source. Everything is in the right place in the folder, but the import doesn't work? I've even added the right path in my compiler for sailing. I get this error.
[code]src\server\game\players\ActionHandler.java:8: error: cannot find symbol import server.game.minigames.sailing; ^ symbol: class sailing location: package server.game.minigames src\server\game\players\ActionHandler.java:86: error: cannot find symbol Sailing.startTravel(c, 1); ^ symbol: variable Sailing location: class ActionHandler src\server\game\players\ActionHandler.java:89: error: cannot find symbol Sailing.startTravel(c, 2); ^ symbol: variable Sailing location: class ActionHandler src\server\game\players\ActionHandler.java:92: error: cannot find symbol Sailing.startTravel(c, 5); ^ symbol: variable Sailing location: class ActionHandler src\server\game\players\ActionHandler.java:95: error: cannot find symbol Sailing.startTravel(c, 6); ^ symbol: variable Sailing location: class ActionHandler src\server\game\players\ActionHandler.java:98: error: cannot find symbol Sailing.startTravel(c, 14); ^ symbol: variable Sailing location: class ActionHandler src\server\game\players\ActionHandler.java:101: error: cannot find symbol Sailing.startTravel(c, 15); ^ symbol: variable Sailing location: class ActionHandler Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. item.title: This SHOULD work but doesn't?
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

mc wobbla:

Already tried. I don’t know what the problem could be, I’ve tried everything…

Your compiler cannot find the symbols, because it cannot find the import. Make sure the import is both packaged right, and make sure your import is leading right to the class file Sailing (or sailing). The capitals and punctuation is key.
